#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.100"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.100:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.100:0.2"
msgid "10. Pupphavagga"
msgstr "10. Flowers"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.100:0.3"
msgid "100. Dutiyagaddulabaddhasutta"
msgstr "100. A Leash (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli3.151"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.100:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.2"
msgid "“Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro."
msgstr "“Mendicants, transmigration has no known beginning."

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.3"
msgid ""
"Pubbā koṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ "
"sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ."
msgstr ""
"No first point is found of sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, "
"hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving."

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.4"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, sā gaddulabaddho daḷhe khīle vā thambhe vā "
"upanibaddho. So gacchati cepi tameva khīlaṃ vā thambhaṃ vā upagacchati; "
"tiṭṭhati cepi tameva khīlaṃ vā thambhaṃ vā upatiṭṭhati; nisīdati cepi tameva "
"khīlaṃ vā thambhaṃ vā upanisīdati; nipajjati cepi tameva khīlaṃ vā thambhaṃ "
"vā upanipajjati."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a dog on a leash was tethered to a strong post or pillar. Whether "
"walking, standing, sitting, or lying down, it stays right beside that post "
"or pillar."

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.5"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, assutavā puthujjano rūpaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, "
"eso me attā’ti samanupassati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, an uneducated ordinary person regards form like this: ‘This "
"is mine, I am this, this is my self.’"

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.6"
msgid "Vedanaṃ …"
msgstr "They regard feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.7"
msgid "saññaṃ …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.8"
msgid "saṅkhāre …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.9"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati."
msgstr "consciousness like this: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self.’"

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.10"
msgid "So gacchati cepi ime pañcupādānakkhandhe upagacchati;"
msgstr "When walking, they walk right beside the five grasping aggregates."

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.11"
msgid "tiṭṭhati cepi ime pañcupādānakkhandhe upatiṭṭhati;"
msgstr "When standing …"

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.12"
msgid "nisīdati cepi ime pañcupādānakkhandhe upanisīdati;"
msgstr "sitting …"

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.13"
msgid "nipajjati cepi ime pañcupādānakkhandhe upanipajjati."
msgstr "lying down, they lie down right beside the five grasping bundles."

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.14"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, abhikkhaṇaṃ sakaṃ cittaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "So you should regularly check your own mind:"

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.15"
msgid "‘dīgharattamidaṃ cittaṃ saṅkiliṭṭhaṃ rāgena dosena mohenā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘For a long time this mind has been corrupted by greed, hate, and delusion.’"

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.16"
msgid "Cittasaṅkilesā, bhikkhave, sattā saṅkilissanti;"
msgstr "Sentient beings are corrupted because the mind is corrupted."

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.17"
msgid "cittavodānā sattā visujjhanti."
msgstr "Sentient beings are purified because the mind is purified."

# See BB’s note for the name of the picture. The commentarial explanation is hardly plausible. Surely the picture must, like very many illustrations in the ancient world, be a pedagogic device, where various kinds of conduct are depicted, perhaps with their results.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.100:2.1"
msgid "Diṭṭhaṃ vo, bhikkhave, caraṇaṃ nāma cittan”ti?"
msgstr "Mendicants, have you seen the picture called ‘Conduct’?”"

msgctxt "sn22.100:2.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

# It is of course impossible to capture in English the pun here between citta = mind and citta = colorful.
msgctxt "sn22.100:2.3"
msgid ""
"“Tampi kho, bhikkhave, caraṇaṃ nāma cittaṃ citteneva cittitaṃ. Tenapi kho, "
"bhikkhave, caraṇena cittena cittaññeva cittataraṃ."
msgstr ""
"“That picture was elaborated by the mind, but the mind is even more "
"elaborate than that."

msgctxt "sn22.100:2.4"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, abhikkhaṇaṃ sakaṃ cittaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "So you should regularly check your own mind:"

msgctxt "sn22.100:2.5"
msgid "‘dīgharattamidaṃ cittaṃ saṅkiliṭṭhaṃ rāgena dosena mohenā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘For a long time this mind has been corrupted by greed, hate, and delusion.’"

msgctxt "sn22.100:2.6"
msgid "Cittasaṅkilesā, bhikkhave, sattā saṅkilissanti;"
msgstr "Sentient beings are corrupted because the mind is corrupted."

msgctxt "sn22.100:2.7"
msgid "cittavodānā sattā visujjhanti."
msgstr "Sentient beings are purified because the mind is purified."

# MS punctuation is wrong, I have corrected it.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli3.152"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.100:3.1"
msgid ""
"Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, aññaṃ ekanikāyampi samanupassāmi evaṃ cittaṃ yathayidaṃ, "
"bhikkhave, tiracchānagatā pāṇā."
msgstr ""
"I don’t see see any other order of beings as elaborate as the animal realm."

msgctxt "sn22.100:3.2"
msgid ""
"tepi kho, bhikkhave, tiracchānagatā pāṇā citteneva cittitā, tehipi kho, "
"bhikkhave, tiracchānagatehi pāṇehi cittaññeva cittataraṃ."
msgstr ""
"The creatures in the animal realm were elaborated by the mind, but the mind "
"is even more elaborate than that."

msgctxt "sn22.100:3.3"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, abhikkhaṇaṃ sakaṃ cittaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "So you should regularly check your own mind:"

msgctxt "sn22.100:3.4"
msgid "‘dīgharattamidaṃ cittaṃ saṅkiliṭṭhaṃ rāgena dosena mohenā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘For a long time this mind has been corrupted by greed, hate, and delusion.’"

msgctxt "sn22.100:3.5"
msgid "Cittasaṅkilesā, bhikkhave, sattā saṅkilissanti;"
msgstr "Sentient beings are corrupted because the mind is corrupted."

msgctxt "sn22.100:3.6"
msgid "cittavodānā sattā visujjhanti."
msgstr "Sentient beings are purified because the mind is purified."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
#. VAR: mañjiṭṭhāya → mañjeṭṭhāya (bj, s1-3, km) | mañjeṭṭhiyā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.100:4.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, rajako vā cittakārako vā rajanāya vā lākhāya vā "
"haliddiyā vā nīliyā vā mañjiṭṭhāya vā suparimaṭṭhe phalake vā bhittiyā vā "
"dussapaṭṭe vā itthirūpaṃ vā purisarūpaṃ vā abhinimmineyya sabbaṅgapaccaṅgiṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose an artist or painter had some dye, red lac, turmeric, indigo, or "
"rose madder. And on a polished plank or a wall or a canvas they’d create the "
"image of a woman or a man, complete in all its various parts."

msgctxt "sn22.100:4.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, assutavā puthujjano rūpaññeva abhinibbattento "
"abhinibbatteti, vedanaññeva … pe … saññaññeva … saṅkhāreyeva … viññāṇaññeva "
"abhinibbattento abhinibbatteti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when an uneducated ordinary person creates a future life, "
"all they create is form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness."

msgctxt "sn22.100:4.3"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn22.100:4.4"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn22.100:4.5"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.100:4.6"
msgid "“Vedanā …"
msgstr "“Is feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.100:4.7"
msgid "saññā …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.100:4.8"
msgid "saṅkhārā …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.100:4.9"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "consciousness permanent or impermanent?” …"

msgctxt "sn22.100:4.10"
msgid "“tasmātiha, bhikkhave … pe …"
msgstr "“So you should truly see …"

msgctxt "sn22.100:4.11"
msgid "evaṃ passaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "Seeing this …"

msgctxt "sn22.100:4.12"
msgid "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānātī”ti."
msgstr "They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.100:4.13"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
